  ### ClassGraph vs. Java Introspection
  
  ClassGraph has the ability to "invert" the Java class and/or reflection API, or has the ability to index classes and resources. For example, the Java class and reflection API can tell you the superclass of a given class, or the interfaces implemented by a given class, or can give you the list of annotations on a class; ClassGraph can find **all classes that extend a given class** (all subclasses of a given class), or **all classes that implement a given interface**, or **all classes that are annotated with a given annotation**. The Java API can load the content of a resource file w
