[tool-exec] update id=call_o8kn8IrbkAv5GpZe7OaOTLxx|fc_0e9fc8c4e7056b01016a58f1dd949c8191add6b7ae60898206 name=bash
  --- 750 ---
  Support GraalVM native images
  When building a "native" application with classgraph `4.8.154`, using GraalVM `22.3` and `JDK 17`, the final generated image fails to run with the following:
  
  ```
  Exception in thread "main" java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Method "getLayer" could not be invoked: java.lang.NoSuchMethodException: Could not find method java.lang.Module.getLayer
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.reflection.ReflectionUtils.invokeMethod(ReflectionUtils.java:231)
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classpath.ModuleFinder.findModuleRefsFromCallstack(ModuleFinder.java:227)
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classpath.ModuleFinder.<init>(ModuleFinder.java:284)
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classpath.ClasspathFinder.<init>(ClasspathFinder.java:164)
  	at io.github.classgraph.Scanner.<init>(Scanner.java:166)
  	at io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scanAsync(ClassGraph.java:1531)
  	at io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scanAsync(ClassGraph.java:1559)
  	at io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scan(ClassGraph.java:1584)
  	at io.github.classgraph.ClassGraph.scan(ClassGraph.java:1623)
  ```
  
  ...and...
  
  ```
  Caused by: java.lang.RuntimeException: Could not find canHandle method for nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.AntClassLoaderHandler
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry$ClassLoaderHandlerRegistryEntry.<init>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:163)
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry$ClassLoaderHandlerRegistryEntry.<init>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:134)
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.<clinit>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:47)
  	... 14 more
  Caused by: java.lang.NoSuchMethodException: nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.AntClassLoaderHandler.canHandle(java.lang.Class, nonapi.io.github.classgraph.utils.LogNode)
  	at java.base@17.0.5/java.lang.Class.getDeclaredMethod(DynamicHub.java:2675)
  	at nonapi.io.github.classgraph.classloaderhandler.ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry$ClassLoaderHandlerRegistryEntry.<init>(ClassLoaderHandlerRegistry.java:159)
  	... 16 more
  ```
  
  In a Spring Boot/Spring world, fixing these would require something akin to the following:
  
  ```java
  public class MyRuntimeHints implements RuntimeHintsRegistrar {
      public MyRuntimeHints() {
      }
  
      @Override
      public void registerHints(final RuntimeHints hints, final ClassLoader classLoader) {
          hints.reflection().registerType(java.lang.Module.class, MemberCategory.INVOKE_DECLARED_METHODS);
      }
  }
  ```
  
  ...which in the end generates AOT JSON metadata for reflection as such:
  
  ```json
    {
      "name": "java.lang.Module",
      "allDeclaredMethods": true
    }
  ```
  
  ...and this would have to be repeated for `AntClassLoaderHandler`, and likely many others. 
  
  This JSON metadata is ideally found and provided by the project itself, so the AOT engine can just pick up up what it needs without having each consumer project declare and configure reflection metadata on their own. Alternatively, there is https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata which allows contributors to push this sort of configuration into a global repository that may be used by AOT engines and appropriate build plugins. 
  
  Before reaching out to graalvm-reachability-metadata, I figured to ask: Is this something classgraph might be open to supporting out of the box, whereby native-image configuration would be maintained and hosted here directly and then released? 
  
  
  
  
  
